The paper deals with the problem of evaluating and optimizing ranking policies for web systems, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of click models to construct efficient estimators suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.CY). Finally, the analysis and evaluation of the proposed estimators involve statistical inference (cs.SI).
